<article>
    <h1>Ac&#xAD;tivist Joshua Wong granted bail in HK</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201001/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-01"><time>2020-10-01</time></a>
        - <span>WORLD</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>HONG KONG • Hong Kong democ­racy ac­tivist Joshua Wong was granted bail yes­ter­day af­ter be­ing for­mally charged in court in con­nec­tion with par­tic­i­pat­ing in an unau­tho­rised assem­bly in Oc­to­ber last year and vi­o­lat­ing an anti-mask law.</p>
    <p>The court de­ci­sion comes as Wong and other ac­tivists face pros­e­cu­tion on sus­pi­cion of sev­eral of­fences re­lated to anti-gov­ern­ment protests last year, which prompted Bei­jing to im­pose a sweep­ing na­tional se­cu­rity law on Hong Kong on</p>
    <p>June 30.</p>
    <p>The 23-year-old Wong, who was ar­rested on Sept 24, was de­fi­ant. His case was ad­journed un­til Dec 18.</p>


